Food delivery from The Coffee Club in Thailand

The Coffee Club is an highly popular Australian brand founded by 2 friends, Emmanuel Drivas and Emmanuel Kokoris, from Brisbane in 1989. They wanted to create a hip place for people to meet for coffee and a bite to eat that was sophisticated yet casual and comfortable. Since opening the doors to their first Coffee Club they have become one of Australia’s largest café groups. Today they have over 400 restaurants in 9 countries and boast 40 million loyal customers. Expanding to Thailand in 2010, each Coffee Club offers great service, gourmet comfort food and a welcoming ambient atmosphere. You can also order online, via foodpanda, from their impressive menu for delivery direct to your front door or to your workplace.

The Coffee Club’s popular dishes

The Coffee Club menu includes an eclectic mix of Thai and European cuisines as well as healthy options, from breakfast, brunch and lunch to evening meals and filling snacks. Their breakfast range includes such delights as Bangkok Eggs Benedict, Poached Eggs with Avocado and a tasty Mushroom, Feta and Spinach Omelette. During your mid-day break try a low cal fresh salad, an appetising sandwich or a fantastic burger. The Coffee Club menu includes wholesome main meals such as Italian pasta, Thai curries and scrumptious fish dishes.

  • ✓ The Big Breakfast: bacon, chipolata sausages, mushrooms, hashbrowns and tomatoes served with a choice of scrambled, poached or fried egg.
  • ✓ Classic Carbonara: spaghetti in a creamy bacon, chicken, garlic, mushroom and egg sauce, topped with Parmesan cheese.
  • ✓ Fat Boy Angus Burger: signature burger that comes with a double veal burger, double cheese and oodles of mustard mayonnaise.
